# Typography Rules for Nine98 App

## üéØ Core Rule

**ALWAYS use Typography component** - Never use raw `<Text>` from React Native.

```typescript
import { Typography } from '@/shared/components/Typography';
```

## üìù Quick Reference

### Text Hierarchy

| Use Case      | Component              | Default Styling                  |
| ------------- | ---------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| Screen Title  | `<Typography.H1>`      | `text-2xl font-bold`             |
| Section Title | `<Typography.H2>`      | `text-xl font-bold`              |
| Subsection    | `<Typography.H3>`      | `text-lg font-bold`              |
| Card Title    | `<Typography.H4>`      | `text-base font-bold`            |
| Body Text     | `<Typography.Body>`    | `text-base`                      |
| Small Text    | `<Typography.Small>`   | `text-sm` + `secondary`          |
| Caption       | `<Typography.Caption>` | `text-xs` + `secondary`          |
| Form Label    | `<Typography.Label>`   | `text-sm font-medium` + `normal` |
| Helper Text   | `<Typography.Helper>`  | `text-xs` + `secondary`          |
| Error         | `<Typography.Error>`   | `text-xs` + `error`              |
| Success       | `<Typography.Success>` | `text-xs` + `success`            |

### Color Variants

Use `variant` prop for semantic colors:

- `primary` (default) - Main text color
- `secondary` - Muted/secondary text
- `normal` - Normal emphasis
- `error`, `success`, `warning`, `info` - Status colors
- `tint` - Accent color

## ‚úÖ DO's

```typescript
// Screen title with spacing
<Typography.H1 className="mb-6">Profile</Typography.H1>

// Secondary text
<Typography.Body variant="secondary">Last updated 2 hours ago</Typography.Body>

// Form pattern
<Typography.Label className="mb-1">Email</Typography.Label>
<TextInput />
<Typography.Helper className="mt-1">We'll never share your email</Typography.Helper>

// Status messages
{error && <Typography.Error className="mt-2">{error}</Typography.Error>}
```

## ‚ùå DON'Ts

```typescript
// WRONG - Raw Text
<Text>Don't use this</Text>

// WRONG - Inline styles
<Typography.Body style={{ color: 'red' }}>No inline styles</Typography.Body>

// WRONG - Hardcoded colors
<Typography.Body className="text-red-500">Use variants instead</Typography.Body>
```

